label.value: Millimole per Liter

value.value: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one thousandth of a mole (10E-3 mole) of solute per one liter of solution.

label.value: CDISC System Organ Class

value.value: Terms at the highest level of the CDISC system organ class terminology.

label.value: Genomic Feature Physical Location

value.value: The physical location on a specified chromosome of a feature or area of interest expressed as a base pair position.

label.value: Malignant Mediastinal Nongerminomatous Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: An extragonadal nongerminomatous malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum.  This category includes embryonal carcinoma, yolk sac tumor, choriocarcinoma, and mixed germ cell tumors.

label.value: Methylene Blue

value.value: A synthetic basic dye. Methylene blue stains to negatively charged cell components like nucleic acids; when administered in the lymphatic bed of a tumor during oncologic surgery, methylene blue may stain lymph nodes draining from the tumor, thereby aiding in the visual localization of tumor sentinel lymph nodes. When administered intravenously in low doses, this agent may convert methemoglobin to hemoglobin.

label.value: Mediastinal Choriocarcinoma

value.value: An extragonadal malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum and is composed of syncytiotrophoblasts, cytotrophoblasts, and intermediate trophoblasts.  The prognosis is usually poor.

label.value: Glottic Cancer TNM Finding v6

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of glottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lip and oral cavity cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Mediastinal Embryonal Carcinoma

value.value: An extragonadal malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum and is composed of primitive large cells with clear or granular cytoplasm forming solid, glandular, or papillary patterns.  It usually affects young males.  It manifests with respiratory distress, thoracic or shoulder pain, fever, cough, superior vena cava syndrome, or hoarseness.

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with tumor size 2 centimeters or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with tumor size more than 2 centimeters, but not more than 4 centimeters in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with tumor size more than 4 centimeters in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Lip cancer with tumor invading through cortical bone, inferior alveolar nerve, floor of mouth or skin of face (i.e. chin or nose). Superficial erosion of bone or tooth socket by a gingival primary tumor is not sufficient to classify as T4. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Oral cavity cancer with tumor invading adjacent structures (e.g. through cortical bone, into deep [extrinsic] muscle of the tongue [genioglossus, hyoglossus, palatoglossus, and styloglossus], maxillary sinus, skin of face). (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with tumor involving the masticator space, pterygoid plates, or skull base and/or encases the internal carotid artery. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lip and oral cavity cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lip and oral cavity cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Mediastinal Mixed Embryonal Carcinoma and Teratoma

value.value: An extragonadal non-seminomatous malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum and contains teratoma and embryonal carcinoma components.

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, more than 3 cm, but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with metastasis in two or more ipsilateral nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with metastasis to one or more lymph nodes, more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lip and oral cavity cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with no distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lip and Oral Cavity Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lip and oral cavity cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Mediastinal Yolk Sac Tumor

value.value: An extragonadal non-seminomatous malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum. It is characterized by the presence of small pale cells with small amount of cytoplasm and round to oval nuclei with small nucleoli forming a variety of patterns, including microcystic, macrocystic, pseudopapillary, myxomatous, hepatoid, polyvesicular vitelline, and solid.  It manifests with respiratory distress, thoracic pain, fever, and superior vena cava syndrome.

label.value: Protein or Enzyme Type Measurement

value.value: A term that refers to a chemistry test measuring a specific protein or enzyme in the peripheral blood or body fluid.
